Caso sin errores de medicin

### Generacin de f y x independientes
set.seed(123)
n<-100 #total de datos

# parmetros de las betas que simulan x y f
sh1x<-2 
sh2x<-2
sh1f<-2
sh2f<-2

# simulamos x y f independientes
x<-rbeta(n, shape1=sh1x, shape2=sh1x, ncp = 0)
f<-rbeta(n, shape1=sh1f, shape2=sh1f, ncp = 0)

# calculamos y
y<-f*(1-x)+x

# graficamos para explorar
plot(x,y)

plot(x,f)

plot(f,y)

# correlacionamos para explorar
cor(x,y)
## [1] 0.5860686
cor(x,f)
## [1] -0.1542397
cor(y,f)
## [1] 0.6569575
# Calculamos hatf y barf, comparamos
hatf<-(mean(y)-mean(x))/(1-mean(x))
barf<-mean(f)

print(paste(hatf,barf))
## [1] "0.520044560265257 0.504706699307929"

Caso con errores de medicin

### Generacin de fo, xo e yo a partir de f y x independientes, x e y con errores

set.seed(123)
n<-100 #total de datos


sh1x<-2
sh2x<-2
sh1f<-2
sh2f<-2
x<-rbeta(n, shape1=sh1x, shape2=sh1x, ncp = 0)
f<-rbeta(n, shape1=sh1f, shape2=sh1f, ncp = 0)

varx<-sh1x*sh2x/((sh1x+sh2x+1)*(sh1x+sh2x)^2)
  
y<-f*(1-x)+x

ex<-rnorm(n,mean=0,sd=varx/10)
ey<-rnorm(n,mean=0,sd=varx/10)
  
xo<-x+ex
yo<-y+ey
fo<-(yo-xo)/(1-xo)

# graficamos para explorar
plot(xo,yo)

plot(xo,fo)

plot(fo,yo)

cor(xo,yo)
## [1] 0.587461
cor(xo,fo)
## [1] -0.1690778
cor(yo,fo)
## [1] 0.6403786
# Calculamos hatf y barf, comparamos
hatfo<-(mean(yo)-mean(xo))/(1-mean(xo))
barfo<-mean(fo)

print(paste(hatfo,barfo))
## [1] "0.519850280042925 0.502895259373664"
